physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Examination revealed dolichocephaly with marked macrocephaly, short neck, corneal clouding, and stiffness of joints. Coarse facial characteristics included a large and depressed nasal bridge, flared nostrils, ocular hypertelorism, dental malocclusion, interdental spacing, thick eyelids, and big, thick lips. The abdomen was soft and non-tender with an umbilical stump, and the liver was palpable 3 cm below the costal margin with a liver span of 10 cm. Respiratory examination revealed bilateral equal air entry with left infra-axillary and infra-scapular crepitations.
